WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.970 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:13.370 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.370 --> 00:00:17.030 align:middle line:84%
>> So I grew up with two
immigrant Indian parents that

00:00:17.030 --> 00:00:21.470 align:middle line:84%
came to America really trusting
of the American food system,

00:00:21.470 --> 00:00:23.840 align:middle line:84%
and really wanting
to be American.

00:00:23.840 --> 00:00:26.540 align:middle line:84%
And so me and my
brother growing up,

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.700 align:middle line:84%
we could eat whatever we
wanted when we were little.

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:32.600 align:middle line:84%
So if I wanted McDonald's,
I got McDonald's.

00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:34.460 align:middle line:84%
If I wanted Wendy's
or Burger King,

00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:39.890 align:middle line:84%
I would get those Happy Meals
every single day if I wanted,

00:00:39.890 --> 00:00:42.320 align:middle line:84%
because it was cheap, it
was readily available,

00:00:42.320 --> 00:00:45.110 align:middle line:84%
and it was food
that we were eating.

00:00:45.110 --> 00:00:46.700 align:middle line:90%
I was really picky child.

00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:49.760 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to eat the
home-cooked Indian meal

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:52.460 align:middle line:84%
my mom was making for
herself and my dad.

00:00:52.460 --> 00:00:53.450 align:middle line:90%
It looked funny.

00:00:53.450 --> 00:00:54.980 align:middle line:90%
It smelled funny.

00:00:54.980 --> 00:00:57.080 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if I'd known
what I know now

00:00:57.080 --> 00:00:59.450 align:middle line:84%
about all the medicinal
curries and the health

00:00:59.450 --> 00:01:02.870 align:middle line:84%
qualities of
vegetarian cooking, I

00:01:02.870 --> 00:01:04.550 align:middle line:84%
would be a totally
different person.

00:01:04.550 --> 00:01:08.360 align:middle line:84%
But I really think I had to get
through that stage in my life

00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:10.820 align:middle line:84%
to get to where I am today and
to make the impact that I'm

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:11.620 align:middle line:90%
making today.

00:01:11.620 --> 00:01:17.000 align:middle line:84%
Because as a result of my
terrible food habits growing up

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.180 align:middle line:84%
and my lack of education
about nutrition,

00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:24.020 align:middle line:84%
it led to a lot of
different health issues.

00:01:24.020 --> 00:01:28.550 align:middle line:84%
And those health issues,
overcoming asthma, eczema,

00:01:28.550 --> 00:01:32.690 align:middle line:84%
allergies, endometriosis,
having my appendix taken out,

00:01:32.690 --> 00:01:36.050 align:middle line:84%
all of those episodes of
being in and out of hospitals

00:01:36.050 --> 00:01:40.010 align:middle line:84%
and doctor's offices
really created passion

00:01:40.010 --> 00:01:43.340 align:middle line:84%
in me to start taking
back control of my health,

00:01:43.340 --> 00:01:47.810 align:middle line:84%
and to make it a
priority to figure out

00:01:47.810 --> 00:01:49.850 align:middle line:90%
what I'd been doing wrong.

00:01:49.850 --> 00:01:53.930 align:middle line:84%
And when I started to question
all the things that I'd

00:01:53.930 --> 00:01:55.640 align:middle line:84%
been taught about
food and started

00:01:55.640 --> 00:01:59.600 align:middle line:84%
to do my own research into
what was truly healthy,

00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:01.940 align:middle line:90%
my mind was blown.

00:02:01.940 --> 00:02:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I found out that
the majority of food

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:06.590 align:middle line:84%
that I'd been eating for
most of my life was dead,

00:02:06.590 --> 00:02:09.229 align:middle line:84%
processed food, that
it had been invented

00:02:09.229 --> 00:02:12.290 align:middle line:84%
in a laboratory full
of different chemicals,

00:02:12.290 --> 00:02:15.770 align:middle line:84%
largely not even
tested for human use,

00:02:15.770 --> 00:02:18.620 align:middle line:84%
just approved by
the manufacturer

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:21.800 align:middle line:84%
themselves instead of the FDA,
no one really even looking

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:24.020 align:middle line:90%
over these chemicals.

00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:28.910 align:middle line:84%
And that I was eating this
non-food in abundance.

00:02:28.910 --> 00:02:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And no wonder my body was
sick, because it wasn't getting

00:02:31.490 --> 00:02:33.410 align:middle line:90%
the nutrients it needed.

00:02:33.410 --> 00:02:36.860 align:middle line:84%
And so when I started to
make radical changes, started

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:39.590 align:middle line:84%
to reduce the amount of
processed foods in my diet,

00:02:39.590 --> 00:02:44.900 align:middle line:84%
started to eat a whole
plant-based, organic, whole

00:02:44.900 --> 00:02:48.680 align:middle line:84%
foods diet, my body
completely changed.

00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:51.650 align:middle line:84%
Not only did I get off all
of my prescription drugs,

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:54.370 align:middle line:84%
which I was on eight at
one point in my life,

00:02:54.370 --> 00:02:57.530 align:middle line:84%
I, for the first time, was
able to maintain my weight

00:02:57.530 --> 00:03:01.550 align:middle line:84%
without dieting, really try
to take a hold of my energy,

00:03:01.550 --> 00:03:05.910 align:middle line:84%
started to feel better than I've
ever felt in my entire life.

00:03:05.910 --> 00:03:08.840 align:middle line:84%
And it was a way of
life that I couldn't

00:03:08.840 --> 00:03:11.840 align:middle line:84%
believe that other people
were not following.

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:14.690 align:middle line:84%
And so I was
shouting everything I

00:03:14.690 --> 00:03:17.600 align:middle line:84%
was learning through the
rooftops to my friends,

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:19.310 align:middle line:84%
through my family,
and they started

00:03:19.310 --> 00:03:20.900 align:middle line:90%
calling me the food police.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:23.163 align:middle line:84%
They were really upset
when I'd go to their houses

00:03:23.163 --> 00:03:24.830 align:middle line:84%
and start looking
through their pantries

00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:27.440 align:middle line:84%
and pointing out all of the
different chemical additives

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:30.170 align:middle line:84%
that they were eating and what
those chemical additives were

00:03:30.170 --> 00:03:33.440 align:middle line:84%
doing to their body and all
the risks associated with them.

00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:38.070 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, they had
enough, and so I said, well,

00:03:38.070 --> 00:03:40.280 align:middle line:90%
why don't I start a blog?

00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:42.272 align:middle line:84%
Why don't I share
this information

00:03:42.272 --> 00:03:43.730 align:middle line:84%
that I'm learning
to the people who

00:03:43.730 --> 00:03:47.150 align:middle line:84%
really are the willing, the
ones who want to change.

00:03:47.150 --> 00:03:49.400 align:middle line:84%
And when I started
doing that, not only

00:03:49.400 --> 00:03:51.050 align:middle line:84%
did a lot of my
friends and my family

00:03:51.050 --> 00:03:55.430 align:middle line:84%
get on board as a result,
but we created a movement.

00:03:55.430 --> 00:03:58.040 align:middle line:84%
And I was working in
the corporate world

00:03:58.040 --> 00:04:03.890 align:middle line:84%
at the time in a very
high-stress, six-figure job

00:04:03.890 --> 00:04:06.380 align:middle line:84%
where I was reporting
to C-level executives

00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:09.890 align:middle line:84%
at some of the biggest financial
institutions in the world.

00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And on the other hand, at home,
when I'd get home from work,

00:04:14.390 --> 00:04:18.050 align:middle line:84%
I would literally not watch
TV, gave up television

00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:21.800 align:middle line:84%
so that I could research and
write and share information

00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:23.870 align:middle line:84%
about the chemicals
in food, and what

00:04:23.870 --> 00:04:25.520 align:middle line:84%
I was learning about
the food industry,

00:04:25.520 --> 00:04:28.490 align:middle line:84%
and what I was doing with my
own body, and all the recipes

00:04:28.490 --> 00:04:30.240 align:middle line:90%
I was making at home.

00:04:30.240 --> 00:04:35.450 align:middle line:84%
And when I started to realize
that that passion for getting

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:39.050 align:middle line:84%
people to stop their
suffering, because I

00:04:39.050 --> 00:04:41.090 align:middle line:84%
had suffered so much
in my life and really

00:04:41.090 --> 00:04:43.580 align:middle line:84%
my mission was to
stop unnecessary

00:04:43.580 --> 00:04:45.190 align:middle line:90%
suffering all of a sudden.

00:04:45.190 --> 00:04:48.140 align:middle line:84%
And I realized my job,
my six-figure salary,

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:51.380 align:middle line:84%
my way of life in
that corporate world

00:04:51.380 --> 00:04:55.070 align:middle line:84%
had such little meaning
compared to helping

00:04:55.070 --> 00:04:57.020 align:middle line:90%
people end that suffering.

00:04:57.020 --> 00:04:59.480 align:middle line:84%
And eventually,
a year and a half

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:02.330 align:middle line:84%
after starting the blog,
quit my job cold turkey,

00:05:02.330 --> 00:05:05.840 align:middle line:84%
was not making any money
being the Food Babe

00:05:05.840 --> 00:05:08.900 align:middle line:84%
or writing as the Food
Babe under this name,

00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:11.180 align:middle line:84%
because I really wanted
to hide my identity.

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:12.810 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want my
bosses to figure out

00:05:12.810 --> 00:05:16.865 align:middle line:84%
who I was or anyone
else for that matter.

00:05:16.865 --> 00:05:18.240 align:middle line:84%
I was really scared
to be online.

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:21.360 align:middle line:84%
I was never on social media
even before starting the blog.

00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:23.725 align:middle line:84%
And so you just
weren't on social media

00:05:23.725 --> 00:05:26.100 align:middle line:84%
as a corporate citizen, because
you didn't want your boss

00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:27.630 align:middle line:90%
to find your personal pictures.

00:05:27.630 --> 00:05:30.990 align:middle line:84%
And you didn't spend time
on Facebook and Twitter

00:05:30.990 --> 00:05:32.070 align:middle line:90%
as a corporate citizen.

00:05:32.070 --> 00:05:35.400 align:middle line:84%
And so for me this
was a whole new world.

00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:39.240 align:middle line:84%
And what happened is as soon
as I started to really branch

00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:41.700 align:middle line:84%
out and tell people who
I am after I quit my job,

00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:45.180 align:middle line:84%
things started to
happen magically.

00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:49.530 align:middle line:84%
Not only did I take on
one of the largest food

00:05:49.530 --> 00:05:50.820 align:middle line:90%
manufacturers in the world--

00:05:50.820 --> 00:05:52.710 align:middle line:84%
Kraft Food-- for
the artificial food

00:05:52.710 --> 00:05:55.590 align:middle line:84%
dyes that they were
using in their products,

00:05:55.590 --> 00:05:59.940 align:middle line:84%
but I suddenly became a
spotlight, a feature all

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:03.060 align:middle line:84%
over the news internationally
for this work,

00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:07.710 align:middle line:84%
and started to highlight issues
about the ethical and moral

00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:09.600 align:middle line:90%
standards of food development.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:13.938 align:middle line:84%
For example, we found out that
one of my first investigations

00:06:13.938 --> 00:06:15.480 align:middle line:84%
that I did as soon
as I quit my job--

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:18.360 align:middle line:84%
because suddenly I
had all of this time--

00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:21.240 align:middle line:84%
was to compare products being
sold in the United States

00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:22.590 align:middle line:90%
to other parts of the world.

00:06:22.590 --> 00:06:26.310 align:middle line:84%
And we found out that our
own American companies

00:06:26.310 --> 00:06:29.670 align:middle line:84%
were reformulating
our favorite products

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:32.790 align:middle line:84%
to be healthier for
citizens overseas and not

00:06:32.790 --> 00:06:33.930 align:middle line:90%
for their own Americans.

00:06:33.930 --> 00:06:36.940 align:middle line:84%
And one product was Kraft
macaroni and cheese,

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:39.510 align:middle line:90%
which in Europe, if it has--

00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:42.390 align:middle line:84%
if a product has
artificial food dyes,

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:44.790 align:middle line:84%
it says may cause adverse
effects on activity

00:06:44.790 --> 00:06:46.160 align:middle line:90%
and attention in children.

00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:48.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, Kraft Foods
had figured that out,

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:51.810 align:middle line:84%
said we're not going to put a
warning label on our products

00:06:51.810 --> 00:06:52.960 align:middle line:90%
overseas.

00:06:52.960 --> 00:06:56.460 align:middle line:84%
We're just going to take out
that artificial food dye.

00:06:56.460 --> 00:07:03.020 align:middle line:84%
And that stance to only
take out artificial food

00:07:03.020 --> 00:07:05.210 align:middle line:84%
dye for some citizens
across the globe

00:07:05.210 --> 00:07:07.730 align:middle line:84%
and not all citizens
across the globe

00:07:07.730 --> 00:07:09.960 align:middle line:84%
is completely immoral
and unethical.

00:07:09.960 --> 00:07:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Because if they know that
there is an ingredient that

00:07:12.860 --> 00:07:17.060 align:middle line:84%
could be risky to children, or
could be harmful to children,

00:07:17.060 --> 00:07:21.320 align:middle line:84%
or contribute to ADHD, or
contribute to hyperactivity,

00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:24.260 align:middle line:84%
I think food corporations
have an obligation

00:07:24.260 --> 00:07:26.760 align:middle line:84%
to make their products as
healthy across the board.

00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And so pointing out
that discrepancy

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:35.150 align:middle line:84%
opened up a Pandora's box of
food activism and social media

00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:38.720 align:middle line:84%
frenzy of moms and
dads and everyone

00:07:38.720 --> 00:07:42.680 align:middle line:84%
sharing this information
so voraciously to the point

00:07:42.680 --> 00:07:44.570 align:middle line:84%
where these
corporations couldn't

00:07:44.570 --> 00:07:47.020 align:middle line:84%
do anything but listen
to us and start to remove

00:07:47.020 --> 00:07:48.020 align:middle line:90%
some of these chemicals.

00:07:48.020 --> 00:07:51.140 align:middle line:90%
