00:07:51.140 --> 00:07:54.950 align:middle line:90%


00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:57.500 align:middle line:84%
The majority of food
products in grocery stores

00:07:57.500 --> 00:08:00.180 align:middle line:84%
are manufactured for
one reason only--

00:08:00.180 --> 00:08:02.720 align:middle line:84%
to increase profit
of food companies.

00:08:02.720 --> 00:08:04.610 align:middle line:84%
The majority of
food companies that

00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.860 align:middle line:84%
are ruling the food
industry are actually

00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:08.390 align:middle line:90%
American-based companies.

00:08:08.390 --> 00:08:13.670 align:middle line:84%
So they rely on
capitalistic mentalities

00:08:13.670 --> 00:08:18.150 align:middle line:84%
and so their purpose is to
make as much money as possible.

00:08:18.150 --> 00:08:23.180 align:middle line:84%
And when you have that driving
your goals as a food company,

00:08:23.180 --> 00:08:27.740 align:middle line:84%
it's very hard to come back
and make health a priority.

00:08:27.740 --> 00:08:33.409 align:middle line:84%
Because health is real,
natural, whole foods that

00:08:33.409 --> 00:08:35.510 align:middle line:90%
have very little processing.

00:08:35.510 --> 00:08:39.289 align:middle line:84%
And it's cheaper to make
artificial food dyes than use

00:08:39.289 --> 00:08:42.440 align:middle line:84%
dyes from beets, and
carrots, and strawberries,

00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:43.820 align:middle line:90%
and blueberries.

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:46.250 align:middle line:84%
And the food industry
has figured this out

00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:49.970 align:middle line:84%
and they've hired very
intense scientists

00:08:49.970 --> 00:08:52.070 align:middle line:84%
to figure this
stuff out for them.

00:08:52.070 --> 00:08:55.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the same scientists that
created addiction in tobacco,

00:08:55.520 --> 00:08:58.670 align:middle line:84%
they've hired to create
addiction in food.

00:08:58.670 --> 00:09:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And so they're using
our brains and the way

00:09:03.440 --> 00:09:06.560 align:middle line:84%
our body responds to
food to their advantage

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:09.500 align:middle line:84%
to continue for us to
be addicted to really

00:09:09.500 --> 00:09:11.840 align:middle line:90%
super cheap processed food.

00:09:11.840 --> 00:09:15.770 align:middle line:84%
And we're in this never-ending
cycle of purchasing this food,

00:09:15.770 --> 00:09:17.300 align:middle line:84%
thinking we're
going to get full,

00:09:17.300 --> 00:09:18.845 align:middle line:84%
but we're really
empty on nutrition.

00:09:18.845 --> 00:09:22.016 align:middle line:90%
